Dataset¶

Dataset Information:

The dataset is from the results of a chemical analysis of wines grown in the same region in Italy but derived from three different cultivars. The first variable in the dataset indicates the cultivar. The remaining 13 variables are the quantities of 13 constituents found in each of the three types of wines.

  1. Cultivar
  2. Alcohol
  3. Malic acid
  4. Ash
  5. Alcalinity of ash
  6. Magnesium
  7. Total phenols
  8. Flavanoids
  9. Nonflavanoid phenols
  10. Proanthocyanins
  11. Color intensity
  12. Hue
  13. OD280/OD315 of diluted wines
  14. Proline

Dataset Source: https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/datasets/wine

Exercises¶

Exercise Overview

Exercise 7¶

Create a silhouette diagram for the k-means clustering completed in Excercise 5

In [12]:
import matplotlib.cm as cm
ss = skl.metrics.silhouette_samples(df_standardized, y_pred1)
fig, ax1 = plt.subplots(1)
ax1.set_xlim(ss.min(), ss.max()+0.1)
ax1.set_ylim(0, len(ss) + cluster_num * 10 + 10)
y_lower = 10
for i in range(cluster_num):
    ss_i = ss[y_pred1 == i]
    ss_i.sort()
    y_upper = y_lower + ss_i.shape[0]
    color = cm.nipy_spectral(float(i) / cluster_num)
    ax1.fill_betweenx(np.arange(y_lower, y_upper),
                          0, ss_i,
                          facecolor = color, edgecolor = color, alpha=0.7)
    ax1.axvline(skl.metrics.silhouette_score(df_standardized, y_pred1), color = 'r',
               linewidth = 0.3) 
    ax1.text(-0.05, (y_upper + y_lower) / 2, i)
    y_lower = y_upper + 10
ax1.set_title("The silhouette plot for the various clusters.")
ax1.set_xlabel("The silhouette coefficient values")
ax1.set_ylabel("Cluster label")
ax1.set_xticks([0, 0.2, 0.4, 0.6])

tmp_df = df_standardized
tmp_df['Cluster'] = y_pred1

sns.pairplot(tmp_df, hue= 'Cluster')
plt.show()

  • In the "elbow chart", the cluster inertia is the y axis and the number of clusters is the x axis

inertia_i = []
for i in range(1, 11):
    km_i = KMeans(n_clusters = i, init = 'random').fit(df_standardized)
    print(str(i) + "th inertia = " + str(km_i.inertia_))
    inertia_i.append(km_i.inertia_)

plt.plot(np.arange(1,11), inertia_i)
